#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:79
msgid ""
"You can help creating a good default page by copying from others, adjusting "
"to your needs, and giving feedback on what could be improved on other pages "
"as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:81
msgid ""
"Please add your CryptoParty dates to the [global dates list](https://"
"cryptoparty.in/parties/upcoming) even if you don't use the wiki as your main "
"website. Help us show how global the movement ist. You can find a dedicated "
"How-To for [adding your own CryptoParty](https://cryptoparty.in/parties/add-"
"a-date) there."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Outreach"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:88
msgid ""
"Outreach helps you to make it known that a CryptoParty is happening. First "
"you need to think of your \"target audience\". That would be people not "
"encrypting anything yet. They know how to turn on a computer but don't have "
"advanced knowledge on the topic.  Start small. Depending on the number of "
"angels available you probably don't want a hundred people showing up at your "
"first CryptoParty.  Locations tend to come with a community. If they are "
"interested in hosting a CryptoParty then their community is likely "
"interested in attending one. If you manage to make them happy they will tell "
"their friends how amazing it was."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:90
msgid ""
"Announce the CryptoParty on the wiki, the mailing lists, and all other "
"relevant channels at hand. Here are some channels you could use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* online\n"
"  * mailing lists\n"
"  * blog posts\n"
"  * social media\n"
"* offline (see [github.com/cryptoparty/flyers](https://github.com/cryptoparty/flyers) for templates to remix)\n"
"  * flyers\n"
"  * stickers\n"
"  * posters\n"
"  * word of mouth\n"
"  * local media\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:104
msgid ""
"Maybe the location would like to put up poster and flyers in a good spot? "
"Maybe they have a mailing list as well? Consider creating a mailing list and "
"social media accounts for your city. Mailing lists, Diaspora, and Twitter "
"seem to be very popular in the CryptoParty community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:106
msgid ""
"Connecting to the worldwide CryptoParty community can be useful to learn "
"from past experience and bring in new impulses."
msgstr ""

