#, no-wrap
msgid "The Party"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting the scene"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:140
msgid ""
"This might be the most important part. A strength of CryptoParties is that "
"they bring together people of most diverse backgrounds and engage them into "
"learning together and from each other. But this also brings its challenges "
"as people might have different ideas of what entails “being excellent to "
"each other”."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:143
msgid ""
"A first step, even before the party officially starts, is to welcome each "
"person or group individually as they arrive and making sure that they don't "
"feel lonely or lost. This is especially important when the start is delayed, "
"which happens more often than it probably should, but this applies to the "
"whole party. Just make sure everyone is excellent to each other and does "
"things (e.g. having a tea and friendly chat).  Tearing down walls."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "Intro Speech"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:147
msgid ""
"In our experience it is helpful to lay out the general “plan” and potential "
"topics in the beginning."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:149
msgid ""
"The intro speech officially opens the CryptoParty. Depending on your style "
"it can be a rather down-to-earth or more fiery thing. But keep it short "
"(less than 20 minutes) and don't go into the technical details as this is "
"what the individual learning groups are for."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:151
msgid ""
"If you want you can show a video (for example the [CryptoParty intro video]"
"(https://github.com/cryptoparty/video))."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:153
msgid "Potential talking points can be"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:177
msgid "hello and welcome"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:177
msgid "thanking the people from the location"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:177
msgid "be excellent to each other"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:177
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* what is CryptoParty\n"
"  * global and decentral movement\n"
"  * everyone can be a part of it\n"
"  * one topic per table\n"
"  * people choose topic\n"
"* security disclaimer\n"
"  * 100% security not possible (neither offline nor online)\n"
"  * using crypto is legal, but not in every country\n"
"  * CryptoParty is for beginners\n"
"  * forward journalists, activists to real experts (e.g. [EFF](https://www.eff.org/), [Tactical Tech](https://tacticaltech.org/), [AccessNow](https://www.accessnow.org/))\n"
"* prejudice that crypto is hard exists\n"
"* security is a process\n"
"  * not a product\n"
"  * not something you install\n"
"  * something you do\n"
"* free software\n"
"  * free as in freedom\n"
"* decentralized services\n"
"  * not controlled by a single company\n"
"* list of topics presented at this specific CryptoParty\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:179
msgid ""
"Don't offer a false sense of security, but also don't scare people with all "
"the ways that things could go wrong. Some people _want_ to hear all the "
"things that could go wrong and are not scared, but you need to figure that "
"out on a person-by-person basis, it's not for the introductory speech."
msgstr ""

