msgid "password security and managers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:197
msgid "Linux installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:197
msgid ""
"[Tails](https://tails.boum.org/) (safe and anonymous operating system... "
"don't forget to tell people to bring a thumb drive)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:199
msgid ""
"A discussion and orientation table would cover how much surveillance is "
"possible and why all of us have something to hide. Most people are not "
"exhibitionists and do value their privacy. Hence it focuses on anyone "
"curious but not yet convinced why they would encrypt or not sure where to "
"start."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:201
msgid ""
"At the discussion and orientation table, you might have to deal with a lot "
"of question you didn't expect. Some of them might even seem irrelevant to "
"you. Don't try to direct the conversation, answer every question without "
"judging instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:202
#, no-wrap
msgid "Asking for help"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:205
msgid ""
"Always ask for help. CryptoParties are not meant to be hard on the "
"individual. If the stress outweights the fun, step back a bit and see how it "
"still magically continues by itself. The main thing for this to happen is "
"toinvite people to help, tell them that they can help and that their help is "
"appreciated. Be it for one CryptoParty or the long run. If you see people "
"show up for the third time in a row, ask them if they want to host a table, "
"if people talk about the bar they work or the house project they live in, "
"ask them if these places would be suitable for a CryptoParty and if they "
"might organize one. The opportunities are plenty."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:207
#, no-wrap
msgid "Variations of the Format"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:210
msgid ""
"CryptoParties for specific groups can help lower the barrier of \"This is "
"not my field of expertise, I won't understand a thing!\". Consider "
"organizing CryptoParties for journalists, students, specific activist "
"groups, etc. Still, even considering the dedicated setup, everyone who "
"happens to come by, should be welcome."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:212
msgid ""
"If you want to reach people who are too shy to attend or if finding a good "
"location is too hard, you might want to offer visiting people at their place "
"for a so-called \"house/living room CryptoParty\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "Roles"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:217
msgid ""
"As with any event there are different roles at a CryptoParty. This chapter "
"will give an overview of all the roles."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:222
msgid "organizers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:222
msgid "intro speakers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:222
msgid "crypto angels"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:222
msgid "meta angels"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:224
#, no-wrap
msgid "Organizer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:227
msgid ""
"As a CryptoParty organizer, you need to find a nice location where people "
"feel comfortable. You keep in touch with the people running the space and "
"find a date suitable for everyone. Locations can be community spaces, cafes, "
"libraries, schools, universities, hackerspaces… any place cozy and inviting "
"with enough chairs, tables, power plugs and fast enough Internet works."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:229
msgid ""
"You could take care of outreach as well to spread the word of when and where "
"the CryptoParty happens. Outreach has a dedicated chapter (see below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:231
msgid ""
"Last but not least you need enough people to explain specific tools and run "
"the CryptoParty with you. If you are experienced you can run with as little "
"as no one and organize the helpers (some call them Crypto Angels) on the "
"spot. But it's way less stressful if you just ask everyone you know who is "
"knowledgable and/or helpful to come."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:233
msgid ""
"Keep groups as small as possible. Experience has shown that the best teacher-"
"learner ratio is 1:5 or lower."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:235
msgid ""
"A CryptoParty is successful if the atmosphere is right. It does not matter "
"how many people showed up. Be patient when starting to establish CryptoParty "
"in your city or community. Spreading the word takes time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:237
#, no-wrap
msgid "Intro Speaker"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:240
msgid ""
"As intro speaker your task is to open the CryptoParty before people move to "
"the table of their choice. It can be be a rather down to earth \"this is "
"what CryptoParty is about and these are the topics\" affair or a fiery \"for "
"your privacy, for our freedom, encrypt now and make the surveillance "
"bastards cry\" rally speech. Every speaker has their own style."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:242
msgid "For notes on talking points see the //Intro Speech// section below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:244
#, no-wrap
msgid "Crypto Angels"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:247
msgid ""
"As Crypto Angel your task is to explain crypto on a conceptual level, what "
"it protects from (or doesn't) and help with installing and using the related "
"software."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:249
msgid ""
"Always explain to the person in your group with the least pre-knowledge, "
"keep an eye out for startled faces and ask if everyone followed after you "
"finish a thought. Encourage interaction and questions whenever they arise. "
"When someone else knows the answer let them answer first."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:252
msgid ""
"Learning should be hands-on first. Never touch a participants computer "
"unless not doing so would really hinder the experience and always ask "
"permission to do so first. Most people are visual learners so drawing little "
"pictures or diagrams can help them a lot grasping the abstract concepts "
"behind the software.  If you don't know the answer to a question, either "
"forward it to the larger crowd/other Crypto Angels, or try to find it with "
"the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:254
msgid ""
"The idea is that people know how to use the tool they learned about on a "
"basic level when they leave the CryptoParty. And even better, that they can "
"then tell their friends they now use \"tool xyz\" and thus get them to "
"understand that it can't be as hard as they previously thought (and then "
"explain it to them, too)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:256
msgid "If you need more Crypto Angles, find them:"
msgstr ""

