#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:261
msgid "at a CryptoParty"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:261
msgid "among your friends"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:261
msgid "at a hackerspace"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:261
msgid "in university"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:263
#, no-wrap
msgid "Meta Angel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:266
msgid ""
"The bigger or more chaotic a CryptoParty is in general, the better it is to "
"have a Meta Angel, a person who's only task is to make sure that everyone "
"has the best learning experience and no one is left alone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:268
msgid ""
"As meta angel you don't have a topic or table. Instead you have an overview "
"of the angels available, what their strengths are, and what table covers "
"which topic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:270
msgid "You help late comers finding a table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:272
msgid ""
"You facilitate communication between tables. Assume there's a question at a "
"table and the local angel has no answer to it. You help them find someone "
"else who might."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:274
msgid "If someone seems to have dropped out help them find the right table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:276
msgid ""
"If someone is undecided about what they want to learn, you can have a chat "
"with them to help them to understand what they'd like to learn and to choose "
"their table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:278
#, no-wrap
msgid "Community Building"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:281
msgid ""
"Things you can do to help grow the local and global CryptoParty community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:282
#, no-wrap
msgid "Regular Meeting Night"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:285
msgid ""
"In order to build a sustainable movement, you want people to form social "
"bonds. A regular meeting night for crypto angels, organizers, etc might "
"serve that purpose. Have fun and share."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:286
#, no-wrap
msgid "Training Sessions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:289
msgid ""
"Angels need a chance to learn some things themselves. At a CryptoParty "
"there's usually not exactly time for this. Hence organizing a \"train the "
"trainer\" session can be a good idea."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conferences"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:293
msgid ""
"There's been a CryptoParty assembly at the CCC congress since the movement "
"started. It helped us a lot to connect worldwide and exchange experiences."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/chapter_00_introducing_cryptoparty/05_how_to_cryptoparty.md:295
msgid ""
"Applying the concept to more conferences can help spread the word. And of "
"course it's lots of fun to meet other like minded people. Or maybe someone "
"already had the same idea and you join forces?"
msgstr ""

